    You can use a CSS module in React. Below is the Javascript code for a file named Home.js
 import styles from &#39;./Home.module.css&#39;;const Home = ()=&gt;{ return( &lt;div className = {styles}&gt; &lt;/div&gt; );}export default Home;
 And in a css module named Home.module.css (format is [name].module.css), put the following and your page will have a background colour of blue
    Make a wrapper componenet with an id like &#34;wrapper&#34; and then create a style with the color state:
 getInitialState: function () { return { color: &#34;white&#34; }; // Set your color for initial state.},changeColor: function () { this.setState({ color: &#34;black&#34; }); // Set your changed color.},render: function () { var style = { backgroundColor: this.state.color }; // The wrapper (root) component return ( &lt;div id=&#34;fullscreen&#34; style={style}&gt; &lt;a onClick={this.changeColor}&gt;change&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt; );}
